## File Responsibilities

| Path | Responsibility |
|------|----------------|
| `cursor-orchestrator/extension.ts` | Entry point; activate(); registers DashboardProvider, orchestrator.initWorkspace command |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/state/types.ts` | All shared TypeScript types: FeatureStatus, TaskStatus, AgentRole, Feature, Task, Handoff, AuditEntry, PMCommand |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/state/ProjectStore.ts` | Read/write `{workspace}/.ai-workspace/project.json` |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/state/FeatureStore.ts` | Read/write `{workspace}/.ai-workspace/features.json` |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/state/TaskStore.ts` | Read/write `{workspace}/.ai-workspace/tasks.json` |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/state/AuditLog.ts` | Append JSONL to `{workspace}/.ai-workspace/audit-log.jsonl` |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/orchestrator/StateMachine.ts` | VALID_TRANSITIONS map, canTransition(), transition() |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/orchestrator/TransitionGuard.ts` | validate(transition, context) — blocks invalid state changes |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/agents/prompts/pm.ts` | buildPMPrompt(context) → LanguageModelChatMessage[] |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/agents/parsers/outputParser.ts` | parseAgentOutput(raw, schema) → Result<T, ParseError>; zod schemas |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/agents/AgentRunner.ts` | runAgent(role, prompt) → calls vscode.lm, parses, logs to AuditLog |
| `cursor-orchestrator/src/ui/DashboardProvider.ts` | Registers sidebar webview; loads webview dist; postMessage bridge |
| `cursor-orchestrator/webview/src/App.tsx` | Mounts PMChat; handles message from host |
| `cursor-orchestrator/webview/src/panels/PMChat.tsx` | User input, message list, send button |
| `cursor-orchestrator/webview/src/types/messages.ts` | WebviewMessage and HostMessage typed contract |

## Data Flow

1. User types in PM Chat (webview).
2. Webview sends postMessage `USER_MESSAGE` to extension host (DashboardProvider).
3. DashboardProvider calls AgentRunner with PM role and buildPMPrompt(context).
4. AgentRunner calls vscode.lm with the prompt; streams response.
5. AgentRunner parses response with outputParser (zod); gets PMCommand.
6. DashboardProvider (or orchestrator) applies command: e.g. CREATE_FEATURE → FeatureStore.
7. StateMachine/TransitionGuard validate; FeatureStore and AuditLog write to disk.
8. AgentRunner sends postMessage `AGENT_REPLY` to webview.
9. Webview renders reply in message list.

Workspace root for `.ai-workspace/`: `vscode.workspace.workspaceFolders?.[0]?.uri.fsPath`.
